{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcc070ae81d148616b2954", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 20, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff02b295b085ab6ebf6"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64634cba0194a6ffd0fd1034", "title": "NEET 2023 (All India)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "Which of the following stages of meiosis involves division of centromere?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "s0l8A", "text": "Telophase", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "mAq1P", "text": "Metaphase I", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "WFRL6", "text": "Metaphase II", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "KyA4j", "text": "Anaphase II", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<blockquote><p>During the anaphase-I of meiosis-I, there is separation of homologous chromosomes to the forming daughter cells. However, the centromere division does not take place at this stage. During anaphase-II or meiosis II, there is splitting of the centromere. Basically, anaphase-II&nbsp;begins with the simultaneous splitting of the centromere&nbsp;of each chromosome (which holds the sister chromatids together),&nbsp;allowing them to move towards opposite poles of the cell by&nbsp;shortening of microtubules attached to kinetochores.</p></blockquote>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ60495885", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["616057290283de43c87e3e1a", "616057b00283de43c87e3e20", "64d50cd33df7f4a7f3017f71", "66b79bbbd4b564dfab4f94d2", "